Evidence-based analysis underpins priority identification needed to guide the trade agenda and the Aid for Trade needs of LDCs. These analytical studies help LDCs determine their biggest constraints to trade integration, prioritize actions to address them accordingly and serve as a basis for the development community to provide trade-related support.
The objective of the Interim Facility is to maintain and build on the results of the EIF until any future multilateral support mechanism for the LDCs is operational.

The Interim Facility seeks to minimize disruptions and loss of hard-earned gains in institutional and productive capacity namely:
1) Improved trade environment conducive for inclusive and sustainable growth of the LDCs; and
2) Increased exports and access to international markets for the LDCs.
Cambodia Export Diversification and Expansion Program (CEDEP) I: Milled Rice, High-Value Silk, Program Monitoring Function

The project purpose is to support the National Implementation Unit (NIU) to develop its capacity to be able to mainstream trade in the national agenda and maximise the benefit from assistance that will be provided in the form of Aid-for-Trade (AfT) to implement the Diagnostic Trade Integration Study (DTIS) Action Matrix.

Feasibility study on the following products: dates, natron and sesame based on a value chain development approach with the view to making recommendations to the Government of Chad to help identify the products that can better contribute to economic diversification

The project?s expected results are: (a) by strengthening and diversifying exports in the three selected sectors, job creation and poverty reduction will be positively affected; (b) to assist the Government in reducing the country?s vulnerability to possible future external shocks by focusing on strengthening current exports and expanding and diversifying the export base; (c) a positive impact on Government-Private Sector dialogue and enhanced responsiveness of both to their respective needs and responsibilities; and (d) continued support to the Government?s efforts to build its capacity to monitor, manage and lead the implementation of its Aid for Trade.
